<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1419] AbstractNonBlockingServer does not catch errors when invoking the processor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1419</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Only exceptions are caught when invoking the processor. If an error is thrown, it causes the thread to die silently without setting the frame buffer state. The client can hang forever waiting for a response.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12529930">THRIFT-1419</key>
